data.story: Under Armour teamed up with A$AP Rocky to create the rapper's first signature sneaker, the SRLo (Skate Rave Lo). The AWGE x SRLo 'Triple Black' pieces together leather and mesh in its upper with exaggerated, reflective eyestays providing a focal point. Raised lettering on the tongue identifies the collaboration. The shoe is supported by UA's HOVR technology and finished with rubber tread. This sample shoe surfaced in February 2018 ahead of the official release in September.

data.story: Designed to commemorate the year Under Armour was created (1996), this colorway uses high-quality materials and premium construction to form a retro look. The Forge 96 boasts a white mesh and nubuck leather upper with an adaptive, breathable fit, as well as black accents on the toe box, ankle and tongue and orange details on the eyestay and lining. The sneaker also sports a one-piece EVA foam midsole, reflective features and an EVA-molded sockliner.

Under Armour Curry 4 Low Nothing But Nets
data.story: Steph Curry’s fourth signature shoe with Under Armour is inspired by his partnership with the United Nations Foundation’s Nothing But Nets movement, which aims to end malaria worldwide. The low-top construction features an all-red makeup, while the shoe’s upper includes a knit sleeve to create a sock-like fit. The cross-centric outsole pattern aims to enhance traction on the court.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 More Range
data.story: Inspired by Steph Curry’s long-range jump shots, the Curry 4 ‘More Range’ features a mostly black finish on the high-top’s sleek design. Constructed with a sock-like mesh application for adaptable forefoot comfort, the shoe is contrasted with a white outsole, branding and SC30 logo on the midsole.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 More Dimes
data.story: The Curry 4 ‘More Dimes’ released as part of a ‘More’ line of Steph Curry’s signature sneakers, this time representing his ability to spread the ball around. Rendered with a black knit and synthetic upper, the design is accented by hits of gold on the collar tab and midsole branding. A Speed Plate is included for added support, while an icy blue translucent outsole provides traction.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 Home
data.story: Combining leather and knit textiles to form a lightweight and adaptable upper, the Curry 4 ‘More Dubs’ sports the signature Warriors color palette. The shoe also incorporates an anatomical lacing system to reduce the amount of pressure on the forefoot without losing support.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 Overcast Grey
data.story: Celebrating Steph Curry’s prolific scoring ability, the Under Armour Curry 4 ‘More Buckets’ is highlighted by two shades of grey across its knit and synthetic upper. The lighter variation represents the humble beginnings of the multiple-time MVP, while the bolder shade references his present and future accolades. An EVA foam midsole is included underfoot.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 White Gold
data.story: The Curry 4 'More Rings' pack was inspired by Stephen Curry's proclamation "to accomplish a lot MORE this season." The 'White Gold' colorway features a white knit sleeve upper bonded with a white microfiber synthetic quarter panel. It also comes with metallic gold branding, a white EVA foam midsole with speckled gold detailing, and an icy blue translucent outsole. Following its October 2017 limited release, this 'White Gold' model dropped in November 2017 alongside a ‘Black White’ colorway.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 Team Royal
data.story: Under Armour and lifestyle essentials brand Stance teamed up on the Curry 4 with an exclusive design that utilizes the Golden State Warriors’ color scheme, although with a focus on Team Royal. Known as the ‘More Fun’ iteration, the shoe comes complete with a custom pair of Stance socks that also incorporate the same tones with a gradient design.

data.name: Under Armour The Rock Delta Downtown Green
data.story: Endorsed by The Rock in 2017, the Under Armour Project Rock Delta debuted in three colorways including this ‘Downtown Green’ version. Covered in a camo-like print, the high-top design is made from breathable mesh with seamless construction and a supportive ankle collar. Underfoot, the matching midsole is equipped with Charged Cushioning for impact absorption, while the solid rubber outsole delivers enhanced flexibility with deep flex grooves.

data.name: Under Armour The Rock Delta City Khaki
data.story: This iteration of The Rock’s signature training silhouette with Under Armour is built with a high-top design rendered in a tonal City Khaki color palette. The upper is constructed with a lightweight and breathable mesh textile, while Charged technology in the midsole increases explosiveness during high-intensity workouts. Keep an eye out for The Rock’s longhorn logo in black on the heel.

data.name: Under Armour The Rock Delta Black
data.story: Under Armour and Dwayne ‘The Rock’ Johnson teamed up for this UA x Project Rock Delta ‘Black’ in November 2017. Its high-top construction utilizes a seamless breathable mesh on the upper alongside a molded heel cup and a soft foam collar. The shoe also boasts a two-piece Charged Cushioning midsole, reflective detailing for visibility in low-light conditions and a durable rubber outsole with deep flex grooves. This colorway features a black upper and sole unit with grey accents, including on Johnson’s Brahma Bull logo on the heel.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 White Black
data.story: The Curry 4 'More Rings' pack was inspired by Stephen Curry's proclamation "to accomplish a lot MORE this season." The 'Black White' colorway features a black knit sleeve upper bonded with a white microfiber synthetic quarter panel. It also comes with a white EVA foam midsole and an icy blue translucent outsole. Following its October 2017 limited release, this 'Black White' model dropped in November 2017 alongside a 'White Gold’ colorway.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 Champ Pack
data.story: Under Armour released an exclusive pack to highlight the Golden State Warriors’ Championship run. The Curry 4 'More Rings’ Championship Pack features two pairs of the Curry 4, one dressed predominantly in black, the other in white. Both feature a bootie construction and knit internal sleeve. Other design details include a microfiber synthetic quarter panel for lightweight support and dynamic seam taping. The shoes also come with a golf divot tool that doubles as a cigar holder.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 More Magic
data.story: Inspired by the colors of the Bund, the waterfront area in central Shanghai, the Curry 4 is blue-hued colorway that celebrates athlete Steph Curry. The Curry 4 'More Magic' features a sock-like design with mid-cut construction for a snug and personalized fit. The upper comes dressed in a reflective mirrored blue color scheme as a nod to the water in Shanghai. The sneaker also sports black details along the collar, tongue, and heel, as well as red accents on the “SC” lettering and Under Armour branding.

data.name: Under Armour C1N Trainer Chairman
data.story: Cam Newton’s signature C1N silhouette features a mid-top design with a mono-sockliner and knitted Threadborne upper for a lifestyle appeal. Sporting the team colors of the Carolina Panthers, the ‘Chairman’ also implements forefoot and heel straps for support, while the grooved midsole provides cushioning.

data.name: Under Armour ArchiTech Futurist Tom Brady Patriots
C1N 'Hometown'
data.story: Cam Newton’s signature C1N silhouette with Under Armour emerges with a Triple Red color scheme on the ‘Hometown.’ Gold speckling is featured throughout the Threadborne knit on the sock-like upper, and the slip-on construction is enhanced with a forefoot and heel strap. Charged foam in the midsole provides cushioning

data.name: Under Armour The Rock Delta Black Yellow
data.story: The Rock’s collaborative project with Under Armour is designed for workouts, featuring an inner bootie construction and a two-piece Charged midsole. The mostly black design is contrasted with yellow accents on the Under Armour branding on the forefoot and the Brahma Bull logo on the heel. The traction pattern on the outsole sports four horizontal yellow stripes.

data.name: ArchiTech Futurist
data.story: Unveiled in 2017, Under Armour’s aptly named ArchiTech Futurist is the brand’s first foray into 3D-printed footwear. In a clean black and white color combination, the contemporary design boasts a compression lacing system with a modern shroud-style cover and zip enclosure. Its 3D-printed heel structure sports a dynamic lattice pattern that provides enhanced cushioning and support along with rubber outsole pods for traction.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Full Circle
data.story: Paying tribute to Steph Curry's fourth NBA All-star appearance, Under Armour released the Curry 3 Low 'Full Circle' in February 2017 as part of a four-shoe 'All-star collection.' The 'Full Circle' colorway represents Curry's transitions over his career and showcases iconic UA technology including a Threadborne upper to wick away moisture when the game heats up. A purple gradient Charged Cushion midsole helps provide responsiveness while the translucent outsole maintains stability below.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Flight Jacket
data.story: Released in January 2017, the Under Armour Curry 3 ‘Flight Jacket’ features a colorway inspired by aviator flight jackets. Its Artillery Green threadborne upper comes with fused black overlays in high-wear areas and a contrasting orange hue on the laces and tongue branding. The upper is supported by a white sole unit with Charged foam cushioning and a full-length herringbone traction on the outsole.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 3 White Blackout Navy
Under Armour Curry 3Zero Warriors Away
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 3Zer0 gets dressed in the signature colors of the Golden State Warriors, featuring a reinforced mesh upper in Team Royal with contrasting yellow accents on the tongue and midsole. Performance details on Steph Curry’s signature shoe include an adjustable heel cap, a dual-density foam midsole and a TPU shank for enhanced stability through the heel and arch.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 4 Low Elemental
data.story: The fourth iteration of All-Star point guard Steph Curry’s signature collection, the Curry 4 upgrades its predecessors with streamlined tech and design. The Under Armour Curry 4 Low 'Elemental' sneaker features a knit internal sleeve with a microfiber synthetic quarter panel and dynamic seam taping, providing a balanced, lightweight fit. An underfoot speed plate and EVA foam deliver responsive energy, while a concentric outsole enhances traction.

UA Curry 3 Magi
data.story: Released December 26, 2016, the Curry 3 ‘Magi' is based on the biblical story of the Three Kings—or Magi—who visited Jesus in Bethlehem shortly after his birth, bearing gifts of gold, frankincense, and myrrh. Gold threading in the burgundy Threadborne knit upper, gold Under Armor branding on the tongue and gold flaking in the translucent outsole distinguish this colorway. It also boasts a gold-laced carbon fiber shank and a white midsole with Charged Cushioning foam.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Raw Sugar
data.story: As the third signature sneaker for Steph Curry, the Curry 3 was designed to amplify performance. It boasts a lightweight white Threadborne upper with perforations throughout for added breathability, midfoot shanks for stability, and charged cushioning for comfort and shock absorption.

data.name: Curry 3 'Bolt Orange'
data.story: Steph Curry’s Under Armour Curry 3 launched in October 2016. It features a Threadborne upper, which is derived from paracord. It also introduced carbon fiber plates on the lateral and medial side of the shoe, called Meta-Wings, designed to stabilize Curry’s ankle. Underfoot, the Curry 3 comes with an Anafoam and Charged cushioning system. This colorway features a Bolt Orange upper with black accents, a Bolt Orange speckled grey midsole and a translucent outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Davidson
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 3 ‘TCC’ pays homage to Steph Curry’s Davidson College alma mater, featuring a red Threadborne upper built with high-tensile yarn. An Anafoam construction delivers adaptive support, while a meta-wing carbon fiber shank in contrasting black provides stability. A grey foam midsole is supported underfoot by a crisp white rubber outsole.

data.name: Curry 3 'Aqua Camo'
data.story: Launched in 2016, the Under Armour Curry 3 boasts Threadborne on its upper, a flexible material derived from paracord, with carbon fiber plates called Meta-Wings included to improve ankle stability. This ‘Aqua Camo’ colorway features a Team Royal and Carolina Blue camo pattern that wraps around the heel and onto the medial forefoot. It also comes with a Charged midsole and an icy translucent outsole that reveals paint splatter detailing underneath.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 3 Grey Matter Green
UA Curry 3 Reign Water
data.story: Inspired by the free-flowing nature of Steph Curry’s play, the Under Armour Curry 3 ‘Reign Water’ features a Threadborne upper in Neptune, complemented by a navy blue mesh tongue adorned with gold UA branding. The meta-wing carbon fiber shank is inscribed with Curry’s personal signature, while the Charged Cushioning midsole is reinforced underfoot by a translucent rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Dub Nation Heritage
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 3 ‘Dub Nation’ takes inspiration from the Golden State Warriors’ road uniform. The mid-top silhouette sports a Threadborne knit upper finished entirely in Royal Blue, accented with pops of yellow on the laces and an Under Armour logo hit on the tongue. A black carbon fiber shank plate adds stability, while a herringbone pattern outsole in white provides traction.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 1 Lux Mid Suede Downtown Green
UA Curry 2.5 Long Shot
data.story: Under Armour dropped the Curry 2.5 ‘Monkey King’ in honor of Stephen Curry's second annual tour of Asia. Both the name and colorway are nods to Sun Wukong, the hero from the classic Chinese novel Journey to the West. It features a yellow, red, black, and white SpeedForm upper in a pattern inspired by Chinese opera masks. Other details include blue Under Armour branding, a black and red midsole, and a white outsole. It dropped in September 2016 alongside the ‘Sky Hound’ colorway.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 Long Shot
data.story: Influenced by Steph Curry’s annual trips to Asia, the Curry 2.5 ‘Sky Hound’ borrows inspiration from China’s fashion scene, featuring an exotic design that resembles the patterns on Chinese opera masks. The shoe itself is formed with a seamless upper construction with a neoprene collar, while the insole sports a ceremonial stamp to commemorate the trip.

data.name: Curry 2.5 'Red Ice'
data.story: Under Armour released an exclusive iteration of the Curry 2.5 with fiery details. The Curry 2.5 'Red Ice' features an engineered mesh upper in an all-over Red Ice color scheme. The sneaker also boasts a lace-up closure for a lockdown fit, contrasting white Under Armour branding on the tongue and lateral heel, and a speckled midsole made with Charged technology.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 1 Mid Lux Blackout Navy
data.story: One of the most memorable of Under Armour’s Curry 1 Lux Mid colorways, this version of Steph Curry’s signature mid-top sees the shoe’s upper dipped entirely in supple blue suede. Prominent stitching, metal eyelets, and a robust metallic gold heel counter give the shoe an elevated look atop a Charged Cushioning system and outsole in complementary blue shades.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Lux Black Gum
data.story: The Under Armour Curry Lux, representing Steph Curry’s first ever lifestyle shoe, debuted in this Black/Gum colorway in August 2016. Based on the Curry One silhouette, the high-top is made for off-court wear, featuring a leather upper in a sleek black finish. Leather lining adds to the premium feel, while the external heel counter and Charged Cushioning midsole contribute to the shoe’s stable fit.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Lux Red
data.story: The Curry 1 Lux Mid Suede emerges as part of Under Armour’s Lux Collection, featuring a tonal suede design for a sophisticated look. This particular rendition implements a ‘Triple Red’ color palette with matte UA and Curry branding throughout, while gold accents appear on the upper eyelets and lace aglets. The Charged midsole unit delivers cushioning.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low Lux Tan
data.story: Under Armour gave the Curry 1 Low a premium update with this August 2016 release. The Curry 1 Lux Low Suede ‘Desert’ showcases a lux suede upper in Desert with a matching Charged midsole. The minimalist build is complemented by a number of performance benefits, including a midfoot TPU shank and an external heel counter. Metal aglets and a leather lining add to the refined look.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Lux White Gum
data.story: Dubbed one of the NBA's most 'unguardable' players, Steph Curry has led the Golden State Warriors to three NBA titles. Honoring his legacy, Under Armour created the Curry 1 Lux Mid Leather lifestyle silhouette. Built with a Nappa leather upper and aerodynamic in appearance, the luxury shoe boasts gold eyestays giving a pop of color to the monochrome, white upper. The 'White Gum' version features a White Charged Cushioning midsole and traction-ready Gum outsole for stability.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 USA
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2.5 sports a patriotic colorway, featuring a primarily navy hue throughout the sleek upper design. Underlying red and white accents emerge throughout the synthetic paneling. The shoe sits atop a speckled Charged midsole, with the patterned outsole completing the American colorway.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Lux Black
data.story: Under Armour debuted the Curry 1 Lux Mid ‘Black Suede’ with a lifestyle offering that features a luxurious twist on the performance basketball shoe. The suede construction of the upper is given a Triple Black finish, accented only by the gold accents on the upper eyelets. Steph Curry’s ‘SC’ branding is tonally applied to the tongue and heel.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 2.5 Finals
data.story: Steph Curry’s 2.5 silhouette with Under Armour showcases the ‘Finals’ color palette, which features an assortment of blues, pinks and greens inspired by the 2016 NBA Finals against the Cleveland Cavaliers. The shoe’s high-top construction is also paired with a Charged midsole unit. ‘SC’ branding appears below the eyelets.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 49ers
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2.5 pays tribute to a different Bay Area team, featuring a color palette reflecting the team colors of the San Francisco 49ers. The red upper, which also sports streaks of black, is covered by gold PU shell. Gold specks appear on the Charged foam midsole, while the herringbone outsole is finished in red. The shoe itself was the first in Steph Curry’s range of signature silhouettes to incorporate an asymmetrical lacing.

data.name: Curry 2.5 'Top Gun'
data.story: Finished in a black and charcoal colorway, the Under Armour Curry 2.5 offers subtle improvements on its predecessor, including a molded synthetic upper that wraps around the foot. Other performance benefits include Under Armour’s Charged Cushioning technology in the midsole, along with a herringbone pattern outsole that delivers enhanced traction on the hardwood.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 Low SC 30 Select
data.story: In the summer of 2016 after the NBA Finals, Steph Curry hosted the SC Select Basketball Camp. Under Armour created an exclusive pack of Curry 2s with a color palette inspired by the camp. This silhouette incorporates a low-top construction with custom Select Camp branding, as well as a Charged midsole for responsive cushioning.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 SC30 Select
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2.5 received a special makeover in honor of Steph Curry’s summer basketball camp. The Curry 2.5 'SC30 Select Camp' features a molded synthetic upper dressed in a Blue Heat color scheme. The sneaker also sports Midnight Navy accents on the nylon collar, leather lining, and on the speckled Charged midsole. Taxi details on the outsole complete the look.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 Dub Nation
data.story: Much like Steph Curry himself, the Curry 2.5 is a technical wonder, packing massive innovation into the high-top hoops shoe. The upper is made from a UA SpeedForm synthetic material that molds to the foot for a precision fit, while die-cut antimicrobial liners boast an anti-friction technology that keeps the foot cool, dry and comfortable. Its sturdy outsole has a multidirectional traction pattern for cutting, pivoting and jumping in any direction.

data.name: Curry 1 'Back to Back'
data.story: Under Armour released the Curry 'Back to Back' pack in June 2016 to honor Steph Curry's consecutive MVP victories in his 2014-2016 seasons with the Golden State Warriors. The Curry 1, sold together with the Curry 2 iteration, focuses on Curry-inspired graphic designs on a foam upper. 'I can do all things,' among Curry's other favorite sayings, display across the shoe. Down below, a revolutionary Charged Cushioning system provides ultimate energy return on and off the court.

data.name: Curry 2 'Back to Back'
data.story: Unveiled as a tribute to Steph Curry's two 'Back to Back' MVP tiles with the Golden State Warriors, the Curry 2 joins the Curry 1 for Under Armour's June 2016 release of the 'Back to Back' sneaker pack. This basketball shoe honors Curry's dominance on the court with metallic gold to black gradient on the SpeedForm upper. 'MVP' shines in gold on the tongue while Under Armour branding on the midfoot and Charged Cushioning midsole sparkle with the same hue.

data.name: UA Curry 2.5 73-9
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2.5 ’73-9’ celebrates the Golden State Warriors’ record-breading 73-9 regular season, with a combination of white, yellow and Team Royal on the molded synthetic upper that’s lifted directly from Golden State’s home uniform. The shoe sports an external PU cage for support, while a Charged midsole leads to a herringbone outsole underfoot.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Waves
data.story: Inspired by Marvel’s Silver Surfer, the Under Armour Curry 2 ‘Waves’ features a wavy white and metallic silver pattern on its SpeedForm upper. Accented by blue on the branding and eyelets, a metallic silver high-abrasion skin is featured on the toe tip, while the underside of the tongue sports a Silver Surfer graphic. The shoe sits on a white full-length Charged Cushioning midsole and a herringbone outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Black Knight
data.story: These Batman-inspired Curry 2 sneakers switch out Warriors gold for a black and yellow scheme fit for Gotham City. The ‘Dark Knight’ rendition sports a black-based upper with yellow accents throughout. Finishing off the superhero-theme is a signature graphic resembling the Bat Signal inside the tongue.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low Chef
data.story: Under Armor cooked up this Curry 2 Low ‘Chef' in June 2016. The white and silver low-top comes equipped with a SpeedForm upper, an external heel counter and a midfoot shank for stability. It also features a high-abrasion skin on the toe tip, while a full-length Charged Cushioning midsole is supported underfoot by a multi-directional herringbone outsole.

data.name: Curry 2 'Gold Rings'
data.story: Under Armor released this ‘Gold Rings’ Curry 2 colorway in June 2016, right before Steph Curry’s second consecutive appearance in the NBA Finals with the Golden State Warriors. The shoe features a Warriors-inspired white SpeedForm upper with blue and metallic gold accents, while the inner tongue tag features a gold 2015 World Champion ring design. A full-length Charged midsole sits underfoot.

data.name: UA Curry 2 USA
data.story: Under Armour released an exclusive colorway to pay tribute to Steph Curry’s participation in the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio. The Curry 2 'USA’ is dressed in a patriotic color scheme, with red accents on the side branding, midsole, and laces, a white UA SpeedForm upper for a precise fit, and navy blue details on the laces, heel, and midsole. The sneaker also boasts perforated engineering for breathability, an external heel counter and midfoot shanks for stability, full-length charged cushioning in the midsole, and a multidirectional organic herringbone outsole for superior traction.

data.name: UA Curry Pack Back 2 Back MVP
data.story: This limited edition June 2016 ‘Back to Back’ paid tribute to Stephen Curry’s back-to-back MVP awards in the 69th and 70th NBA seasons. The pack comes with limited edition versions of the Curry 1 ‘MVP’ and Curry 2 ‘MVP.’ The Curry 1 features a gradient fade black and white AnaFoam upper with all-over print detailing, a gold heel counter and a black and white sole. The Curry 2 ‘MVP’ features a black and gold gradient SpeedForm upper with a black heel counter, and a black and gold sole.

data.name: Curry 2 'Mother's Day'
data.story: Under Armour equips the Curry 2 with a ‘Mother’s Day’ color scheme that features a series of pink rose outlines throughout the high-top’s upper. The seamless synthetic base in Light Grey implements perforations throughout to improve airflow, while Under Armour’s Charged compound is included in the midsole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Electric Blue
data.story: The second Under Armour release with Steph Curry, this basketball sneaker sports a Speedform knit upper and a UA Charged foam midsole. The rubber tread is designed for traction on the court, while UA branding graces the side of the shoe. ‘I can do all things’ in Curry’s handwriting is scrawled on the heel shank, part of a Bible verse he writes on all of his gameday footwear. This model sports an Electric Blue upper complemented by Steel, Midnight Navy and a white sole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low San Francisco Giants
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 Low ‘Giants’ steps off the hardwood and onto the baseball diamond, wearing a distinctive color scheme that pays tribute to the Bay Area’s National League baseball team, the San Francisco Giants. Accordingly, the low-top carries a UA SpeedForm upper dressed in a mix of black and orange. The shoe’s tooling has the same color scheme, anchored by a translucent rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low Athletics
data.story: Released alongside a San Francisco Giants iteration as part of the Bay Area Baseball Pack in 2016, Under Armour celebrated the Oakland A’s with this MLB-inspired Curry 2 Low. Based in white, the design sports team colors of green and yellow across its mesh upper, inner lining, heel counter, and Charged sole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low The Essential
data.story: The Curry 2 Low 'Essential' updates the classic Curry 2 Low that first hit shelves in 2016. The sneaker features an engineered mesh upper with breathable panels throughout. The low top also sports patent accents on the mudguard, a synthetic heel counter for durability and support, “I Can Do All Things” quoted on the heel side, and Charged technology in the midsole for responsive cushioning.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low The Hook
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 Low ‘Hook’ features Combat Green coloring on a ventilated mesh upper known as UA SpeedForm, engineered for a precision fit. An external heel counter in black delivers locked-in stability, while a high-abrasion welded overlay atop the toe provides extra support and durability. A full-length Charged Cushioning midsole is good for impact absorption and energy return.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Birthday
data.story: Under Armour released the Curry 2 'Surprise Party' in March 2016 in honor of Stephen Curry’s 28th birthday. The high-top sneaker features a white SpeedForm upper with electric blue Under Armour branding on the tongue and side panel. It also comes with an electric blue full-length Charged Cushioning midsole and matching heel counter. Other details include confetti-inspired accents on the inner lining and herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 3 Chinese New Year
data.story: This limited edition January 2017 Curry 3 ‘CNY’ dropped for Chinese New Year to usher in the Year of the Rooster. The sneaker sports a Rocket Red Threadborne upper alongside metallic gold upper eyelets and Under Armour tongue branding. The festive look also comes with multicolored graphic prints on the heel and midsole, while the white rubber outsole is equipped with a herringbone traction pattern.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Low Energy
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 Low ‘Energy’ launched the low-top version of Steph Curry’s second signature shoe for NBA All-Star Weekend in 2016. The Rocket Red SpeedForm upper sports contrasting black and lime green accents, supported underfoot by Charged cushioning in the black midsole and a herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 All Star (2016)
data.story: Under Armour pays tribute to Stephen Curry with the Curry 2 'All Star', the sneaker he wore at the 2016 NBA All-Star Game. Released in February 2016, the shoe features a white SpeedForm upper with a red inner lining and metallic gold Under Armour branding and hardware. It also boasts a white external heel counter, a full-length white Charged Cushioning midsole, and a gold-speckled, icy translucent herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: UA C1N Cleats MVP  (Unsigned)
data.story: This special edition Under Armour C1N MVP 'Cam Newton' honored Cam Newton’s 2015 NFL MVP award. The iridescent gold high-top features a synthetic upper printed with ‘MVP’ as well as Newton’s stats from his award-winning season. Weighing in at only 12.5 ounces, it also comes with a molded 4D Foam footbed, a gold Pebax cleat plate and a removable ankle strap.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Elite
data.story: Under Armour released the limited edition Curry 2 'Elite' in February 2016. The high-top sneaker features a black SpeedForm upper with a black leather toecap. It is accented with metallic gold hits on the Under Armour branding, laces and sole. Other features include a multicolor tongue lining, a full-length white Charged Cushioning midsole, and a gold-speckled icy blue translucent herringbone outsole.

data.name: Curry 2 GS 'The Storm'
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 GS appears in a tonal colorway known as ‘The Storm,’ featuring a breathable knit upper throughout the subdued high-top construction. Designed to provide stability throughout the ankle, a sock-like fit also provides snug support. A Charged midsole is included for cushioning, while the only hit of color comes via the inside of the tongue and the insole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Haight Street
data.story: Under Armour pays tribute to San Francisco’s Haight Ashbury district with the Curry 2 ‘Haight Street’ from January 2016. It features an Electric Blue and white SpeedForm upper with a custom Haight Street inner tongue tab. It also boasts a Midnight Navy external heel counter, a full-length Charged midsole and a white herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low Championship
data.story: This Curry One Low celebrates Stephen Curry's 2015-16 three-point contest, MVP, and NBA Championship winning season with the Golden State Warriors. The colorway features a white upper with metallic gold accents, '2015 MVP' branding on the inner tongue, and a golden flaked icy blue translucent outsole. Released in January 2016, the shoe was also restocked in March.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Dub Nation Home
data.story: The Curry 2 ‘Dub Nation’ pays tribute to the sell-out home crowds at Oracle Arena who watched Steph Curry lead the Golden State Warriors to an NBA record 54-straight regular season home wins, spanning from January 31, 2015 to March 29, 2016. Inspired by the Warriors’ home uniform, the colorway features a white SpeedForm upper with Royal and Taxi accents. Underfoot, the shoe sports a Charged midsole and a herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Northern Lights
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 ‘Northern Lights’ features a vibrant gradient finish across its upper, transitioning from Rebel Pink on the toe to Purple Panic on the heel. Contrasting pops of Poison Green appear on the laces and large Under Armour logo that adorns the lateral collar. The aurora borealis-inspired design is finished with ‘North’ inscribed above an illustrated globe inside the tongue.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Rainmaker
data.story: The ‘Rainmaker’ colorway of the Curry 2 emerges with a stormy motif that combines grey and teal tones throughout the design. Featuring a one-piece synthetic construction on the high-top’s upper, with sleek mesh paneling for breathability, the shoe also features the phrase ‘The Storm’ on the inner tongue to reflect Steph Curry’s ability to make it rain.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Suit and Tie
data.story: The Curry 2 ‘Suit and Tie’ pays tribute to Steph Curry’s appearance in GQ magazine in December 2015. He was featured in the magazine after scoring a then-NBA-record 286 three-pointers in the 2014-15 season. The clean cut look features a white and black SpeedForm upper with red accents, with metallic silver branding on the ankle and tongue. Charged Cushioning is included in midsole, while a ‘suit and tie’ graphic appears inside the tongue.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Providence Road
data.story: Ohio-born NBA legend Steph Curry spent the majority of his youth in North Carolina. In this November 2015 collaboration with Under Armour, the Curry 2 silhouette comes dressed in a 'Providence Road' colorway, paying homage to Curry's NC roots. The SpeedForm upper and heel counter take on the NC blue while bright red accents the sock liner, laces and midsole. A flag design on the inner tongue is meant to represent the Tar Heel State.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Long Shot
data.story: The Curry 2 hit shelves in this original ‘Longshot’ colorway named after Stephen Curry’s ability to shoot and score from nearly any place on the court. In black and yellow, the shoe’s upper features Under Armour’s SpeedForm molding for precision fit and perforated engineering for lightness and breathability. Underfoot, a full-length midsole with Charged Cushioning and herringbone-textured outsole deliver responsiveness and floor control.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Professional
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 2 ‘Professional’ is all business, featuring a primarily black and charcoal color palette that lets the tech do the talking. The shoe’s high-top design is complemented with a seamless leather construction on the upper that promotes forefoot flexibility, while ventilation pods keep feet cool. A Charged midsole promotes a responsive stride with optimal cushioning during sharp cuts.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Floor General
data.story: The Curry 2 'Floor General’ dropped ahead of Veteran’s Day in November 2015. The patriotic colorway features a red SpeedForm upper with navy blue on the tongue and collar and a white herringbone outsole. Gold branding appears on the ankle and tongue, as well as on the speckled midsole, while ‘Floor General’ and five gold stars appear on the inside of the tongue.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Father to Son
data.story: Steph Curry’s Curry 2 pays homage to his father’s legacy in the NBA, inspiring him to play in the NBA as well. The shoe’s high-top construction is equipped with a primarily seamless, flexible upper that sports the Charlotte Hornets team colors – the same franchise Steph’s father played for. Additionally, the phrase, “Father to Son” appears on the inside of the tongue.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Dub Nation Away
data.story: Proudly sporting the team colors of the Golden State Warriors, the Under Armour Curry 2 pays tribute to ‘Dub Nation,’ featuring a primarily seamless design throughout the high-top construction. Charged midsole technology provides an explosive response in every step, while creating ample cushioning to combat abrupt movements on the court.

data.name: UA Curry 2 Iron Forges Iron
data.story: The ‘Iron Sharpens Iron’ colorway of the Curry 2 references the idea of two opponents making each other stronger than they were before. The shoe’s Speedform knit upper features a grey base that’s accented with an orange gradient on the Charged midsole, mimicking the notion of forging iron in fire. ‘SC’ branding appears on the medial-side of the forefoot.

data.name: Curry 1 'Championship Pack'
data.story: Steph Curry’s first signature shoe received a two-sneaker pack to celebrate his 2015 MVP season and the Golden State Warriors’ 2015 NBA title. This colorway, the darker of the two, features an all-black upper with yellow accents on the branding. The black Charged midsole leads to yellow outsole.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Championship Pack
data.story: Releasing in October 2015, the Under Armour Curry 1 Championship Pack celebrates Steph Curry’s first NBA title with the Golden State Warriors. Included are two contrasting colorways: ‘Splash Party’ in white, gifted to Steph for his 27th birthday, and the ‘Moment’ colorway in black and yellow—the pair that Curry wore during Game 6 of the Finals, when the Dubs ultimately clinched the championship.

data.name: Team Curry 1 Low 'Royal'
data.story: The Team Curry 1 Low features a lightweight mesh upper dressed in a Racer Blue color scheme with black accents on the lining and heel counter. The low top boasts a foam collar for extra comfort and ankle support, a Charged midsole for responsive cushioning, and a full-length, one-piece marbled rubber outsole with a multi-directional pattern for added traction.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low Elite 24
data.story: The ‘Elite 24’ edition of the Curry 1 Low celebrates the 10th annual Under Armour Basketball Tournament of the same name. Released in 2015, the special edition sports a blue camouflage upper with orange accents covering the laces, tongue, liner and Under Armour branding. The look is topped off by a tonal blue Charged midsole with orange speckling and a white rubber outsole.

data.name: Under Armour Curry 1 Low Two-A-Days
data.story: This Curry 1 Low is also known as the Two-A-Days, a reference to Steph Curry’s off-season training schedule. This low silhouette of the player’s first signature sneaker exhibits a mostly black body with an AnaFoam upper, external heel counter, and Charged Cushioning in the midsole. The multi-directional outsole provides a splash of gray to this dark colorway, along with silver Under Armour logos.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Black and Gold Banner
data.story: Reminiscent of the model Golden State Warriors shooter Stephen Curry wore during the 2015 NBA Finals, this ‘Blackout’ edition of the Under Armour Curry One debuted in August of the same year. The design features a black-on-black AnaFoam upper, UA’s signature Charged cushioning, midfoot shank, heel counter, and a matching herringbone outsole. Gold branding brings the Oakland team colors together.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Golf
data.story: Inspired by Steph Curry’s affinity for golf, the Curry 1 appears with a dark grey base on the upper with contrasting green accents throughout. The mesh tongue offers optimal breathability to keep feet cool, while Charged technology in the midsole enables a responsive stride for sharp cuts on court.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low UAA Finals
data.story: Eye-catching and futuristic, Under Armour's Curry Low 'Bolt Orange,' touts court performance and street appeal. The bright orange, perforated Anafoam upper elicits comfort and breathability while neon green and black accents provide function and flair. A molded black heel counter helps ensure stability and structure, contrasting the speckled green Charged Cushion midsole. Let loose in July 2015, the head-turning silhouette is yet another success in Curry's partnership with UA.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low SC30 Select
data.story: Originally an exclusive for the nation’s top 30 high school point guards invited to attend Steph Curry’s SC30 Select basketball camp, the Curry 1 Low 'SC30 Select’ eventually received a limited release in July 2015. The special edition colorway sports a Hyper Green AnaFoam upper offset by orange on the sidewalls, tongue, lining and outsole. It also boasts a metallic silver heel counter and mudguard atop a Purple Blaze midsole with orange speckled detailing.

data.name: UA Curry 1 SC30 Select

The sneaker implements a Charged midsole unit, while the slanted collar is designed for better ankle mobility.

data.name: UA Curry 1 All American
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 1 ‘All American’ released in July 2015 to coincide with the Under Armour All-America high school basketball game. The design features a metallic gold finish on the dimpled upper, accented with red laces and a molded heel counter in contrasting black. Underfoot, a white midsole is reinforced with an external shank on the medial side for added lateral stability.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low Dub Nation

A TPU shank wraps around the midfoot for extra stability.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Low Panthers
data.story: Under Armour released an exclusive colorway in the colors of the Carolina Panthers to honor Stephen Curry’s favorite team. The Curry 1 Low 'Panthers' features a dimpled AnaFoam teal upper with black overlays on the toe box, collar lining, and heel. The low top also boasts metallic details on the side branding, an integrated lacing system for a lockdown fit, as well as a Charged midsole for responsive cushioning.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Father to Son
data.story: The Under Armour Curry 1 celebrates the story of Steph Curry growing up watching his father Dell play for the Charlotte Hornets, hence this iteration sporting the Charlotte team colors. The upper primarily sports purple, with teal accents appearing on the midsole, toe and heel. The midsole also sports a speckled detailing that makes its way onto to the Under Armour branding near the heel. The shoe is stamped with ‘30|30’ on the lace branding to celebrate both Steph and Dell wearing the number 30 in their professional careers.

data.name: UA Curry 1 MVP
data.story: Introduced in 2015, the Curry 1 is Stephen Curry’s first signature basketball sneaker. It features Charged cushioning in the midsole and a lightweight yet supportive Anafoam upper. This special edition ‘MVP’ colorway dropped to celebrate his first NBA MVP title in 2015 after posting averages of 23.8 points, 7.7 assists and 2 steals per game. The shoe features a gradient fade on its Anafoam upper, from white at the toe to black at the heel. It also boost gold accents that nod to the MVP trophy.

data.name: UA Curry 1 Dub Nation

This Curry 1 colorway draws inspiration from Golden State’s home uniform, featuring a white upper with a speckled blue midsole and bright yellow outsole.
